Their only goal is to earn money to help their families stay at home.
Since 1 December, a law has entered into force, according to which each worker must carry out an examination to check his or her knowledge of the Russian language.
For now, this rule applies only to those who intend to work in the service sector, Community service institutions, domestic services and retail trade.
However, in time, as they promise in the Federal Immigration Service, examinations will be made mandatory for all immigrants.
Furthermore, it will not be sufficient to give the language examination, if not also that of Russian history and that of the foundations of legislation.
Knowledge of the language must be confirmed even to receive and renew the work permit.
It is an exception to the citizens of the countries where Russian is the official language.
This law will not be subject to persons who managed to obtain their certificates of education and diplomas before the dissolution of the Soviet Union in 1991.
Utility, fatality and protection of rights
The network of examining centres will be run by the Russian Language Institute Pushkin, the University of Amistad de los Pueblos, Moscow State University, St. Petersburg State University and other Russian higher education institutions.
Immigrants may present themselves to the tests in all cities, right now in Russia more than 160 such centres are open.
